<eesti>I. &Uuml;lds&auml;tted </eesti>
<inglise>I General Provisions </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 1. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 1. </inglise>
<eesti>Puhkuseseaduse &uuml;lesanded </eesti>
<inglise>Purpose of Holidays Act </inglise>
<eesti>Eesti Vabariigi puhkuseseadus reguleerib suhteid, mis tekivad t&ouml;&ouml;taja ja t&ouml;&ouml;andja vahel seoses puhkuse andmisega. </eesti>
<inglise>The Republic of Estonia Holidays Act regulates the relations which arise between employees and employers in connection with the granting of holidays. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 2. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 2. </inglise>
<eesti>Puhkuse m&otilde;iste ja liigid </eesti>
<inglise>Definition and classification of holiday </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Puhkus t&auml;hendab t&ouml;&ouml;lepingu peatumist k&auml;esoleva seadusega etten&auml;htud korras ja tingimustel. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A holiday means the suspension of an employment contract pursuant to the procedure and under the conditions prescribed in this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) T&ouml;&ouml; iseloomu ja tingimuste j&auml;rgi antavad puhkused on: </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Holidays granted according to the nature of the work and working conditions are the following: </inglise>
<eesti>1) p&otilde;hipuhkus, sealhulgas pikendatud puhkus (k&auml;esoleva seaduse paragrahv 9); </eesti>
<inglise>1) base holiday, including extended holiday (&sect; 9 of this Act); </inglise>
<eesti>2) lisapuhkus (k&auml;esoleva seaduse paragrahv 10). </eesti>
<inglise>2) additional holiday (&sect; 10 of this Act). </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Peale k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi 2. l&otilde;ikes nimetatud puhkuste on k&auml;esoleva seaduse reguleerimisobjektiks: </eesti>
<inglise>(3) In addition to the holidays specified in subsection 2 of this section, this Act regulates: </inglise>
<eesti>1) vanemapuhkused (k&auml;esoleva seaduse paragrahvid 28-31); </eesti>
<inglise>1) leave for parents (&sect;&sect; 28-31 of this Act); </inglise>
<eesti>2) palgata puhkus (k&auml;esoleva seaduse paragrahvid 32-34). </eesti>
<inglise>2) holiday without pay (&sect;&sect; 32-34 of this Act). </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 3. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 3. </inglise>
<eesti>Puhkuse andmine t&ouml;&ouml;aasta eest </eesti>
<inglise>Grant of holidays for working year </inglise>
<eesti>(1) P&otilde;hi- ja lisapuhkust, samuti t&auml;iendavat lapsepuhkust (k&auml;esoleva seaduse paragrahv 31) antakse t&ouml;&ouml;aasta eest. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Base holiday, additional holiday and additional child care leave (&sect; 31 of this Act) are granted per working year. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;aasta on aeg, mis algab selle t&ouml;&ouml;andja juures t&ouml;&ouml;le asumise p&auml;evast ja kestab j&auml;rgmise aasta sama p&auml;evani. </eesti>
<inglise>A working year is a year which commences on the day a person commences work with an employer and continues until the same day of the following year. </inglise>
<eesti>Kui selles ajavahemikus on perioode, mida t&ouml;&ouml;aasta hulka ei arvata, l&uuml;kkub t&ouml;&ouml;aasta l&otilde;pp vastava arvu t&ouml;&ouml;p&auml;evade v&otilde;rra edasi. </eesti>
<inglise>If there are periods of time which are not included in the working year, the end of the working year is postponed by the corresponding number of working days. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;aastast l&uuml;hema aja eest antakse puhkust v&otilde;rdeliselt t&ouml;&ouml;tatud ajaga. </eesti>
<inglise>For periods shorter than a working year, holidays are granted in proportion to the amount of time worked. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Osalise t&ouml;&ouml;ajaga t&ouml;&ouml;tamisel puhkuse kestust ei l&uuml;hendata. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) In the case of part-time employment, the duration of a holiday is not shortened. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 4. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 4. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;aasta arvutamine </eesti>
<inglise>Calculation of working year </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Peale tegelikult t&ouml;&ouml;tatud aja arvatakse t&ouml;&ouml;aasta hulka: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) In addition to actual time worked, a working year includes: </inglise>
<eesti>1) aeg, mil t&ouml;&ouml;taja on ajutiselt t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;imetu; </eesti>
<inglise>1) periods during which an employee is temporarily incapacitated for work; </inglise>
<eesti>2) puhkuse, v&auml;lja arvatud lapsehoolduspuhkuse ja t&ouml;&ouml;taja soovil antud palgata puhkuse aeg; </eesti>
<inglise>2) holidays, except parental leave and holidays without pay granted at the request of an employee; </inglise>
<eesti>3) t&ouml;&ouml;andja ettepanekul antud palgata v&otilde;i osaliselt tasustatava puhkuse aeg (k&auml;esoleva seaduse paragrahv 33); </eesti>
<inglise>3) holidays without pay or with partial pay granted on the proposal of an employer (&sect; 33 of this Act); </inglise>
<eesti>4) t&ouml;&ouml;lepingu ebaseadusliku l&otilde;petamise v&otilde;i ebaseaduslikult teisele t&ouml;&ouml;le &uuml;leviimise t&otilde;ttu t&ouml;&ouml;lt sunnitud puudumise aeg, kui t&ouml;&ouml;taja on t&ouml;&ouml;le ennistatud; </eesti>
<inglise>4) periods of forced absence from work due to the unlawful termination of an employment contract or unlawful transfer to other work, if the employee is reinstated to employment; </inglise>
<eesti>5) muu aeg, mil t&ouml;&ouml;taja on seaduse, haldusakti, kollektiiv- v&otilde;i t&ouml;&ouml;lepinguga etten&auml;htud alustel ajutiselt vabastatud t&ouml;&ouml;&uuml;lesannete t&auml;itmisest. </eesti>
<inglise>5) other periods during which an employee is temporarily released from performing his or her duties on the bases prescribed by law, administrative legislation, a collective agreement or employment contract. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) T&ouml;&ouml;andja &uuml;hepoolse otsusega v&otilde;ib t&ouml;&ouml;aasta hulka arvata ka muu aja, mil t&ouml;&ouml;taja on poolte kokkuleppel ajutiselt vabastatud t&ouml;&ouml;&uuml;lesannete t&auml;itmisest. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) By a unilateral decision of the employer, other periods during which an employee is temporarily released from performing his or her duties by agreement of the parties may also be included in a working year. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 5. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 5. </inglise>
<eesti>Puhkuse ajal t&ouml;&ouml;lepingu l&otilde;petamise piiramine </eesti>
<inglise>Restriction on termination of employment contract during holidays </inglise>
<eesti>Puhkuse ajal ei ole lubatud t&ouml;&ouml;lepingu l&otilde;petamine t&ouml;&ouml;andja algatusel, v&auml;lja arvatud ettev&otilde;tte, asutuse, muu organisatsiooni v&otilde;i t&ouml;&ouml;andja &otilde;igustega struktuuri&uuml;ksuse likvideerimise v&otilde;i t&ouml;&ouml;andja pankrotistumise t&otilde;ttu (t&ouml;&ouml;lepingu seaduse paragrahvi 91 1. l&otilde;ike punkt 2 ja 2. l&otilde;ige, RT 1992, art.241). </eesti>
<inglise>It is prohibited for an employer to initiate termination of an employment contract during a holiday, except due to the liquidation of an enterprise, agency, other organisation or a structural unit with the rights of an employer, or the bankruptcy of the employer (clause 91 (1) 2) and subsection 91 (2) of the Employment Contracts Act, RT 1992, 15/16, 241; 1993, 10, 150; I 1993, 26, 441; 1995, 14, 170; 16, 228; 1996, 3, 57; 40, 773; 45, 850; 49, 953; 1997, 5/6, 32). </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 6. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 6. </inglise>
<eesti>Puhkuse kestuse arvutamine </eesti>
<inglise>Calculation of duration of holiday </inglise>
<eesti>Puhkuse kestust arvutatakse, olenemata t&ouml;&ouml;aja re&zcaron;iimist t&ouml;&ouml;andja juures, kalendrip&auml;evades, mille hulka ei arvata riiklikke p&uuml;hi. </eesti>
<inglise>Regardless of the working time regime with an employer, the duration of a holiday is calculated in calendar days, and does not include public holidays. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 7. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 7. </inglise>
<eesti>Puhkuse pikendamine </eesti>
<inglise>Extension of holiday </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;tajale seaduse v&otilde;i haldusaktiga etten&auml;htud puhkust v&otilde;ib pikendada kollektiiv- v&otilde;i t&ouml;&ouml;lepinguga, samuti t&ouml;&ouml;taja soovil t&ouml;&ouml;andja &uuml;hepoolse otsusega. </eesti>
<inglise>A holiday prescribed for an employee by law or administrative legislation may be extended by a collective agreement or employment contract, or at the request of the employee by a unilateral decision of the employer. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 8. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 8. </inglise>
<eesti>Puhkuse andmise kohustus. </eesti>
<inglise>Duty to grant holiday. </inglise>
<eesti>Puhkusest loobumise kehtetus </eesti>
<inglise>Invalidity of waived holiday </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;andjal ei ole &otilde;igust j&auml;tta puhkust andmata ja t&ouml;&ouml;tajal ei ole &otilde;igust puhkusest loobuda. </eesti>
<inglise>Employers do not have the right to withhold holidays and employees do not have the right to waive holidays. II </inglise>
<eesti>II. P&otilde;hi- ja lisapuhkus </eesti>
<inglise>Base Holiday and Additional Holiday </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 9. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 9. </inglise>
<eesti>P&otilde;hipuhkus </eesti>
<inglise>Base holiday </inglise>
<eesti>(1) P&otilde;hipuhkuse kestus on 28 kalendrip&auml;eva, v&auml;lja arvatud k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi 2. ja 3. l&otilde;ikes etten&auml;htud juhtudel. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The duration of a base holiday is twenty-eight calendar days, except in the cases prescribed in subsections (2) and (3) of this section. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Pikendatud p&otilde;hipuhkust antakse: </eesti>
<inglise>(2) An extended base holiday is granted to: </inglise>
<eesti>1) alaealistele 35 kalendrip&auml;eva </eesti>
<inglise>1) minors, 35 calendar days; </inglise>
<eesti>2) invaliididele 35 kalendrip&auml;eva </eesti>
<inglise>2) disabled persons, 35 calendar days; </inglise>
<eesti>3) riigiametnikele ja kohaliku omavalitsuse ametnikele 35 kalendrip&auml;eva </eesti>
<inglise>3) state officials and local government officials, 35 calendar days; </inglise>
<eesti>4) &uuml;likoolide, rakenduslike k&otilde;rgkoolide, teadusasutuste, koolide ja muude lasteasutuste juhtidele, teaduritele, &otilde;ppej&otilde;ududele, &otilde;petajatele, kasvatajatele ja teistele pedagoogikaspetsialistidele kuni 56 kalendrip&auml;eva </eesti>
<inglise>4) heads, researchers, academic staff, teachers, educators and other pedagogical specialists of universities, institutions of applied higher education, research institutions, schools and other child care institutions, up to 56 calendar days; </inglise>
<eesti>5) raviasutuste, lastesanatooriumide, t&auml;isealiste hoolekandeasutuste pedagoogikaspetsialistidele kuni 56 kalendrip&auml;eva. </eesti>
<inglise>5) pedagogical specialists of medical institutions, children's sanatoriums and adult welfare institutions, up to 56 calendar days. </inglise>
<eesti>(08.10.97 j&otilde;ust.01.01.98 - RT I 1997, 74, 1229) </eesti>
<inglise>(08.10.97 entered into force 01.01.98 - RT I 1997, 74, 1229) </inglise>
<eesti>(2 (1)) Ametikohtade loetelu, kus t&ouml;&ouml;tamisel antakse pikendatud puhkust kuni 56 kalendrip&auml;eva, ja puhkuse kestuse konkreetsel ametikohal kehtestab Vabariigi Valitsus. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) 1 A list of positions where extended holidays are granted for up to 56 calendar days and the duration of holidays for particular positions shall be established by the Government of the Republic. </inglise>
<eesti>(08.10.97 j&otilde;ust.01.01.98 - RT I 1997, 74, 1229) </eesti>
<inglise>(08.10.97 entered into force 01.01.98 - RT I 1997, 74, 1229) </inglise>
<eesti>(3) K&auml;esoleva paragrahviga etten&auml;htud puhkuse kestust ei kohaldata t&ouml;&ouml;tajate suhtes, kelle puhkus on reguleeritud Eesti Vabariigi eriseadusega. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The duration of holidays prescribed in this section is not applied with regard to employees whose holidays are regulated by a specific Act of the Republic of Estonia. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 10. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 10. </inglise>
<eesti>Lisapuhkus </eesti>
<inglise>Additional holiday </inglise>
<eesti>(1) &Otilde;igus lisapuhkusele on t&ouml;&ouml;tajatel: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Employees have the right to an additional holiday if they are engaged in: </inglise>
<eesti>1) allmaat&ouml;&ouml;del; </eesti>
<inglise>1) underground work; </inglise>
<eesti>2) tervistkahjustavatel ja eriiseloomuga t&ouml;&ouml;del. </eesti>
<inglise>2) work which poses a health hazard or work of a special nature. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Allmaat&ouml;&ouml;de ning tervistkahjustavate ja eriiseloomuga t&ouml;&ouml;de n&auml;idustused ja loetelu, kus t&ouml;&ouml;tamisel antakse lisapuhkust ning nende lisapuhkuste kestuse kehtestab Eesti Vabariigi Valitsus. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The Government of the Republic shall establish the indicators and a list of underground work, work which poses a health hazard and work of a special nature where an additional holiday is granted, and the duration of the additional holiday. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Kollektiiv- ja t&ouml;&ouml;lepinguga v&otilde;ib ette n&auml;ha t&auml;iendavad alused lisapuhkuse andmiseks. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Supplementary bases for granting an additional holiday may be prescribed by a collective agreement or employment contract. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 11. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 11. </inglise>
<eesti>Lisapuhkuse andmise tingimused </eesti>
<inglise>Conditions for granting additional holiday </inglise>
<eesti>(1) T&auml;ies ulatuses antakse lisapuhkust t&ouml;&ouml;tajale, kes on allmaat&ouml;&ouml;del v&otilde;i tervistkahjustavatel t&ouml;&ouml;del t&ouml;&ouml;tanud kogu t&ouml;&ouml;aasta. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) An additional holiday is granted in full to employees who have been engaged for an entire working year in underground work or work which poses a health hazard. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;tajale, kes on allmaat&ouml;&ouml;del v&otilde;i tervistkahjustavatel t&ouml;&ouml;del t&ouml;&ouml;tanud osa aega t&ouml;&ouml;aastast, antakse lisapuhkust v&otilde;rdeliselt t&ouml;&ouml;tatud ajaga. </eesti>
<inglise>An additional holiday is granted to employees who have been engaged in underground work or work which poses a health hazard for part of the working year, in proportion to the time worked. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) T&ouml;&ouml;tajale, kellele antakse p&otilde;hipuhkus t&auml;ies ulatuses enne t&ouml;&ouml;aasta t&auml;itumist, antakse koos p&otilde;hipuhkusega lisapuhkus samuti t&auml;ies ulatuses. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Employees who are granted a base holiday in full before the end of a working year are also granted an additional holiday in full, together with the base holiday. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Lisapuhkuse andmise tingimused eriiseloomuga t&ouml;&ouml;del (k&auml;esoleva seaduse paragrahvi 10 1. l&otilde;ike punkt 2) kehtestab Vabariigi Valitsus. (08.10.97 j&otilde;ust.01.01.98 - RT I 1997, 74, 1229) </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The conditions for granting an additional holiday in the case of work of a special nature (clause 10 (1) 2) of this Act) shall be established by the Government of the Republic. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 12. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 12. </inglise>
<eesti>P&otilde;hi- ja lisapuhkuse liitmine </eesti>
<inglise>Adding base holiday and additional holiday </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Lisapuhkus liidetakse p&otilde;hipuhkusele (k&auml;esoleva seaduse paragrahv 9) ja antakse sellega koos. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) An additional holiday is added to and granted together with a base holiday (&sect; 9 of this Act). </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Erinevatel alustel antavad lisapuhkused liidetakse. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Additional holidays granted on different bases are added together. </inglise>
<eesti>III. </eesti>
<inglise>III </inglise>
<eesti>Puhkuse andmise kord </eesti>
<inglise>Procedure for Granting Holidays </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 13. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 13. </inglise>
<eesti>Puhkuse andmine esimesel t&ouml;&ouml;aastal </eesti>
<inglise>Grant of holidays during first working year </inglise>
<eesti>(1) T&ouml;&ouml;tajal, kes on esimesel t&ouml;&ouml;aastal t&ouml;&ouml;tanud v&auml;hemalt kuus kuud, on &otilde;igus saada puhkust v&otilde;rdeliselt t&ouml;&ouml;tatud kuude arvuga. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Employees who have worked at least six months during their first working year have the right to receive a holiday in proportion to the number of months worked. </inglise>
<eesti>Saamata j&auml;&auml;nud puhkuseosa antakse t&ouml;&ouml;aasta kestel m&otilde;nel muul ajal v&otilde;i t&ouml;&ouml;taja n&otilde;usolekul liidetakse j&auml;rgmise t&ouml;&ouml;aasta puhkusega v&otilde;i antakse teise t&ouml;&ouml;aasta kestel m&otilde;nel muul ajal. </eesti>
<inglise>Holiday time which has not been received is granted during the working year at another time, is added to the holiday of the following working year with the consent of the employee, or is granted at another time during the second working year. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) S&otilde;ltumata t&ouml;&ouml;tatud ajast on esimesel t&ouml;&ouml;aastal &otilde;igus saada puhkust t&auml;ies ulatuses: </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Regardless of the amount of time worked, the following have the right to receive a holiday in full during the first working year: </inglise>
<eesti>1) alaealisel; </eesti>
<inglise>1) minors; </inglise>
<eesti>2) invaliidil; </eesti>
<inglise>2) disabled persons; </inglise>
<eesti>3) naisel enne v&otilde;i p&auml;rast rasedus- ja s&uuml;nnituspuhkust; </eesti>
<inglise>3) women before or after pregnancy leave or maternity leave; </inglise>
<eesti>4) mehel, kelle naine on rasedus- ja s&uuml;nnituspuhkusel; </eesti>
<inglise>4) men whose wives are on pregnancy leave or maternity leave; </inglise>
<eesti>5) t&ouml;&ouml;ga seotud tervisekahjustuse j&auml;rgselt t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;ime osaliselt kaotanud t&ouml;&ouml;tajal; </eesti>
<inglise>5) employees who are partially incapacitated for work due to a work-related injury; </inglise>
<eesti>6) muudel seaduse, haldusakti, kollektiiv- v&otilde;i t&ouml;&ouml;lepinguga etten&auml;htud juhtudel. </eesti>
<inglise>6) in other cases prescribed by law, administrative legislation, a collective agreement or employment contract. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Poolte kokkuleppel v&otilde;ib esimesel t&ouml;&ouml;aastal anda puhkust t&auml;ies ulatuses, s&otilde;ltumata t&ouml;&ouml;tatud ajast. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) By agreement of the parties, a holiday may be granted in full during the first working year regardless of the amount of time worked. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 14. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 14. </inglise>
<eesti>Puhkuse andmine teise ja j&auml;rgmiste t&ouml;&ouml;aastate eest </eesti>
<inglise>Grant of holidays for second and subsequent working years </inglise>
<eesti>Puhkust teise ja j&auml;rgmiste t&ouml;&ouml;aastate eest v&otilde;ib anda t&auml;ies ulatuses t&ouml;&ouml;aasta kestel vastavalt poolte kokkuleppele v&otilde;i t&ouml;&ouml;andja juures kehtivale puhkuste ajakavale. </eesti>
<inglise>Holidays may be granted in full for the second or subsequent working years by agreement of the parties or according to the holiday schedule of the employer. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 15. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 15. </inglise>
<eesti>Puhkuste ajakava </eesti>
<inglise>Holiday schedule </inglise>
<eesti>(1) T&ouml;&ouml;andja koostab puhkuste ajakava iga kalendriaasta kohta ja teeb selle t&ouml;&ouml;tajale teatavaks jaanuarikuu jooksul. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Employers shall compose a holiday schedule for every calendar year and communicate it to the employees during the month of January. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Puhkuste ajakava koostamisel l&auml;htub t&ouml;&ouml;andja t&ouml;&ouml; korraldamise huvidest, arvestades v&otilde;imaluse korral t&ouml;&ouml;tajate soove. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Employers shall prepare a holiday schedule based on the interests of work management, taking the wishes of employees into consideration if possible. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) T&ouml;&ouml;andja on kohustatud puhkuste ajakava koostamisel arvestama t&ouml;&ouml;tajate soovidega, kellel on seaduse j&auml;rgi &otilde;igus saada puhkust neile sobival ajal (k&auml;esoleva seaduse paragrahvi 16 punktid 3-6). </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Upon preparing a holiday schedule, employers are required to consider the wishes of employees who by law have the right to receive holidays at a time suitable for them (clause 16 (3) 6) of this Act). </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 16. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 16. </inglise>
<eesti>Puhkuse andmine t&ouml;&ouml;tajale sobival ajal </eesti>
<inglise>Grant of holidays at time suitable for employees </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;taja soovitud ajal on t&ouml;&ouml;andja kohustatud andma puhkust: </eesti>
<inglise>An employer is required to grant a holiday at the time requested by the employee to: </inglise>
<eesti>1) naisele enne ja p&auml;rast rasedus- ja s&uuml;nnituspuhkust v&otilde;i p&auml;rast lapsehoolduspuhkust; </eesti>
<inglise>1) a woman before and after pregnancy or maternity leave or after parental leave; </inglise>
<eesti>2) mehele naise rasedus- ja s&uuml;nnituspuhkuse ajal; </eesti>
<inglise>2) a man during or after the pregnancy leave or maternity leave of his wife; </inglise>
<eesti>3) naisele, kes kasvatab kuni kolmeaastast last; </eesti>
<inglise>3) a woman raising a child of up to three years of age; </inglise>
<eesti>4) mehele, kes &uuml;ksinda kasvatab kuni kolmeaastast last; </eesti>
<inglise>4) a man raising a child of up to three years of age alone; </inglise>
<eesti>5) alaealisele; </eesti>
<inglise>5) a minor; </inglise>
<eesti>6) t&ouml;&ouml;ga seotud tervistkahjustuse j&auml;rgselt t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;ime osaliselt kaotanud t&ouml;&ouml;tajale. </eesti>
<inglise>6) an employee who is partially incapacitated for work due to a work-related injury; </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 17. (Kehtetu - 24.01.2001 j&otilde;ust.01.01.2002 - RT I 2001, 17, 78) </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 17. (Repealed - 24.01.2001 entered into force 01.01.2002 - RT I 2001, 17, 78) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 18. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 18. </inglise>
<eesti>Puhkuse kasutamist takistavad asjaolud </eesti>
<inglise>Circumstances hindering use of holiday </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Puhkuse kasutamist takistavateks asjaoludeks on: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The circumstances hindering the use of a holiday are: </inglise>
<eesti>1) t&ouml;&ouml;taja ajutine t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;imetus; </eesti>
<inglise>1) temporary incapacity for work of an employee; </inglise>
<eesti>2) rasedus- ja s&uuml;nnituspuhkusel viibimine; </eesti>
<inglise>2) pregnancy leave or maternity leave; </inglise>
<eesti>3) riigi- v&otilde;i kohaliku omavalitsusorgani poolt pandud &uuml;lesannete t&auml;itmine. </eesti>
<inglise>3) performance of duties assigned by a state or local government body. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) T&ouml;&ouml;taja on kohustatud t&ouml;&ouml;andjale teatama puhkuse kasutamist takistavatest asjaoludest. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Employees are required to inform the employer of circumstances hindering the use of a holiday. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;andja v&otilde;ib n&otilde;uda puhkuse kasutamist takistavate asjaolude t&otilde;endamiseks dokumente. </eesti>
<inglise>The employer may demand documents proving the circumstances which hinder the use of the holiday. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 19. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 19. </inglise>
<eesti>Puhkuse v&otilde;i puhkuseosa &uuml;leviimine muule ajale seoses puhkuse kasutamist takistavate asjaoludega </eesti>
<inglise>Transfer of holiday or part of holiday to another time due to circumstances hindering use of holiday </inglise>
<eesti>Kui puhkuse kasutamist takistavad asjaolud (k&auml;esoleva seaduse paragrahvi 18 1. l&otilde;ike punktid 1-3) tekkisid enne puhkuse algust, viiakse puhkus &uuml;le poolte kokkuleppega m&auml;&auml;ratud ajale. </eesti>
<inglise>If circumstances hindering the use of a holiday (clauses 18 (1) 1) -3) of this Act) arise before the beginning of the holiday, the holiday is transferred to the time determined by agreement of the parties. </inglise>
<eesti>Kui puhkuse kasutamist takistavad asjaolud tekkisid puhkuse ajal, antakse saamata j&auml;&auml;nud puhkuseosa vahetult p&auml;rast takistavate asjaolude l&otilde;ppemist v&otilde;i viiakse poolte kokkuleppel &uuml;le muule ajale. </eesti>
<inglise>If circumstances hindering the use of a holiday arise during the holiday, the unused holiday time is granted immediately after the hindering circumstances cease to exist or is transferred to another time by agreement of the parties. </inglise>
<eesti>Rasedus- ja s&uuml;nnituspuhkuse t&otilde;ttu puhkuse &uuml;leviimisel teisele ajale kohaldatakse k&auml;esoleva seaduse paragrahvi 16 punkti 1. </eesti>
<inglise>Clause 16 1) of this Act applies upon the transfer of a holiday to another time due to pregnancy leave or maternity leave. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 20. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 20. </inglise>
<eesti>Puhkuse &uuml;leviimine muule ajale poolte kokkuleppel </eesti>
<inglise>Transfer of holiday to another time by agreement of parties </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Poolte kokkuleppel v&otilde;ib puhkuste ajakava muuta ning puhkuse v&otilde;i osa puhkusest &uuml;le viia muule ajale samal t&ouml;&ouml;aastal v&otilde;i j&auml;rgmisele t&ouml;&ouml;aastale. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) By agreement of the parties, a holiday schedule may be changed and a holiday or holiday time may be transferred to another time during the same working year or to the following working year. </inglise>
<eesti>J&auml;rgmisele t&ouml;&ouml;aastale &uuml;leviidud puhkus liidetakse selle t&ouml;&ouml;aasta puhkusega v&otilde;i antakse poolte kokkuleppel m&otilde;nel muul ajal t&ouml;&ouml;aasta kestel. </eesti>
<inglise>Holidays transferred to the following working year are added to that year's holiday or, by agreement of the parties, are granted at another time during the working year. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Kui puhkuse &uuml;leviimist taotleb t&ouml;&ouml;andja ja kokkulepet t&ouml;&ouml;tajaga ei saavutata, on t&ouml;&ouml;tajal &otilde;igus j&auml;&auml;da puhkusele ajakavas etten&auml;htud ajal. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) If an employer requests the transfer of a holiday but no agreement is reached with the employee, the employee has the right to go on holiday at the time prescribed in the schedule. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Alaealisele tuleb anda puhkust igal t&ouml;&ouml;aastal, tema puhkuse &uuml;leviimine j&auml;rgmisele t&ouml;&ouml;aastale on keelatud (v&auml;lja arvatud puhkuse &uuml;leviimine seoses rasedus- ja s&uuml;nnituspuhkusega). </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Minors must be granted a holiday every working year; the transfer of the holiday of a minor to the following working year is prohibited (except for the transfer of a holiday due to pregnancy leave or maternity leave). </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 21. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 21. </inglise>
<eesti>Puhkuse osadena andmine </eesti>
<inglise>Grant of holiday in parts </inglise>
<eesti>Poolte kokkuleppel v&otilde;ib puhkust anda osade kaupa, kusjuures &uuml;he katkestamatu osa kestus peab olema v&auml;hemalt 14 kalendrip&auml;eva. </eesti>
<inglise>By agreement of the parties, a holiday may be granted in parts, in which event the duration of one continuous part must be at least fourteen calendar days. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 22. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 22. </inglise>
<eesti>Puhkuse katkestamine </eesti>
<inglise>Interruption of holiday </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Puhkuse katkestamine ja t&ouml;&ouml;taja t&ouml;&ouml;le tagasi kutsumine v&otilde;ib toimuda poolte kokkuleppel. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A holiday may be interrupted and an employee may be asked to return to work by agreement of the parties. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Puhkuse katkestamise t&otilde;ttu kasutamata j&auml;&auml;nud puhkuse osa antakse poolte kokkuleppel samal t&ouml;&ouml;aastal m&otilde;nel muul ajal v&otilde;i liidetakse j&auml;rgmise t&ouml;&ouml;aasta puhkusega v&otilde;i antakse j&auml;rgmise t&ouml;&ouml;aasta kestel m&otilde;nel muul ajal. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Holiday time which is not used due to the interruption of the holiday is granted at another time during the same working year by agreement of the parties, is added to following year's holiday or is granted at another time during the following working year. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 23. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 23. </inglise>
<eesti>Puhkuse andmise vormistamine </eesti>
<inglise>Formalising grant of holidays </inglise>
<eesti>Puhkus vormistatakse t&ouml;&ouml;andja juures kehtestatud korras. </eesti>
<inglise>Holidays are formalised pursuant to the procedure established by the employer. </inglise>
<eesti>IV. </eesti>
<inglise>IV </inglise>
<eesti>Puhkusetasu ja kasutamata puhkuse rahaline h&uuml;vitamine </eesti>
<inglise>Holiday Pay and Monetary Compensation for Unused Holiday </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 24. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 24. </inglise>
<eesti>Puhkusetasu </eesti>
<inglise>Holiday pay </inglise>
<eesti>P&otilde;hi- ja lisapuhkuse ning t&auml;iendava lapsepuhkuse aja eest maksab t&ouml;&ouml;andja t&ouml;&ouml;tajale puhkusetasu, mille arvutamise korra kehtestab Vabariigi Valitsus. (08.10.97 j&otilde;ust.01.01.98 - RT I 1997, 74, 1229) </eesti>
<inglise>Employers shall pay employees holiday pay for base holiday, additional holiday and additional child care leave, which are calculated pursuant to the procedure established by the Government of the Republic. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 25. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 25. </inglise>
<eesti>Puhkusetasu maksmine </eesti>
<inglise>Payment of holiday pay </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Puhkusetasu makstakse hiljemalt eelviimasel t&ouml;&ouml;p&auml;eval enne puhkuse algust t&auml;ies ulatuses. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Holiday pay is paid in full not later than on the penultimate working day before commencement of the holiday. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) T&ouml;&ouml;taja, kellele ei makstud puhkusetasu k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi eelmises l&otilde;ikes etten&auml;htud ajal, v&otilde;ib n&otilde;uda puhkuse pikendamist puhkusetasu maksmisega viivitatud aja v&otilde;rra. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) An employee who is not paid holiday pay at the time prescribed in the preceding subsection of this section may demand extension of his or her holiday with payment of holiday pay for the period of time the holiday pay is delayed. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 26. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 26. </inglise>
<eesti>Kasutamata puhkuse h&uuml;vitamine t&ouml;&ouml;lepingu l&otilde;ppemisel </eesti>
<inglise>Compensation for unused holidays upon termination of employment contract </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;lepingu l&otilde;ppemisel on t&ouml;&ouml;andja kohustatud t&ouml;&ouml;tajale maksma kasutamata j&auml;&auml;nud puhkuse eest rahalist h&uuml;vitist. </eesti>
<inglise>Upon the termination of an employment contract, the employer is required to pay the employee monetary compensation for unused holidays. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 27. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 27. </inglise>
<eesti>Puhkusetasu maksmise allikad m&otilde;ne kategooria t&ouml;&ouml;tajatele </eesti>
<inglise>Sources of holiday pay for certain categories of employees </inglise>
<eesti>Puhkusetasu ja kasutamata puhkuse rahaline h&uuml;vitus alaealistele ja invaliididele &uuml;le 28 kalendrip&auml;eva antava puhkuse eest (k&auml;esoleva seaduse paragrahvi 9 2. l&otilde;ike punktid 1 ja 2), samuti t&auml;iendava lapsepuhkuse p&auml;evade eest (k&auml;esoleva seaduse paragrahv 31) makstakse riigieelarve vahenditest riikliku sotsiaalkindlustuse eelarve kaudu Sotsiaalministeeriumi poolt kehtestatud korras. </eesti>
<inglise>The holiday pay and monetary compensation for unused holidays of minors and disabled persons for holidays of more than 28 calendar days (clauses 9 (2) 1) and 2) of this Act), and for the days of additional child care leave (&sect; 31 of this Act) are paid from state budget funds through the state social insurance budget pursuant to the procedure established by the Ministry of Social Affairs. </inglise>
<eesti>(15.11.94 j&otilde;ust.01.01.95 - RT I 1994, 84, 1474) </eesti>
<inglise>(15.11.94 entered into force 01.01.95 - RT I 1994, 84, 1474) V </inglise>
<eesti>V. Vanemapuhkused </eesti>
<inglise>Leave for Parents </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 28. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 28. </inglise>
<eesti>Rasedus- ja s&uuml;nnituspuhkus </eesti>
<inglise>Pregnancy leave and maternity leave </inglise>
<eesti>Naisele antakse s&uuml;nnituslehe alusel rasedus- ja s&uuml;nnituspuhkust 70 kalendrip&auml;eva enne ja 56 kalendrip&auml;eva p&auml;rast s&uuml;nnitust. </eesti>
<inglise>Based on a certificate for maternity leave, a woman is granted a pregnancy leave of 70 calendar days before giving birth and a maternity leave of 56 calendar days after giving birth. </inglise>
<eesti>Mitmikute s&uuml;nni v&otilde;i t&uuml;sistustega s&uuml;nnituse korral antakse s&uuml;nnituspuhkust 70 kalendrip&auml;eva. </eesti>
<inglise>In the case of a multiple birth or a delivery with complications, a maternity leave of 70 calendar days is granted. </inglise>
<eesti>Rasedus- ja s&uuml;nnituspuhkus liidetakse ja antakse t&auml;ies ulatuses, s&otilde;ltumata lapse s&uuml;ndimise p&auml;evast. </eesti>
<inglise>Pregnancy leave and maternity leave are added together and granted in full, regardless of the date of birth of the child. </inglise>
<eesti>Rasedus- ja s&uuml;nnituspuhkuse aja eest makstakse h&uuml;vitist vastavalt ravikindlustusseadusele (RT I 1991, 23, 272; 1997, 28, 425). </eesti>
<inglise>Compensation for the period of pregnancy leave and maternity leave is paid pursuant to the Health Insurance Act (RT I 1991, 23, 272; 1997, 28, 425). </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 29. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 29. </inglise>
<eesti>Lapsendaja puhkus </eesti>
<inglise>Adoptive parents leave </inglise>
<eesti>Kuni aastase lapse lapsendajale antakse puhkust 70 kalendrip&auml;eva, alates lapsendamise p&auml;evast. </eesti>
<inglise>An adoptive parent of a child of up to one year of age is granted a leave of 70 calendar days, as of the date of adoption. </inglise>
<eesti>Selle aja eest makstakse h&uuml;vitist vastavalt ravikindlustusseadusele. </eesti>
<inglise>Compensation is paid for this period of time pursuant to the Health Insurance Act. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 30. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 30. </inglise>
<eesti>Lapsehoolduspuhkus </eesti>
<inglise>Parental leave </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Lapse emale v&otilde;i isale antakse tema soovil lapsehoolduspuhkust kuni lapse kolmeaastaseks saamiseni. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A mother or father is granted parental leave at his or her request until the child attains three years of age. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Kui ema v&otilde;i isa ei kasuta lapsehoolduspuhkust, v&otilde;ib puhkuse anda lapse tegelikule hooldajale, kes seaduslikul alusel elab Eesti Vabariigis. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) If a mother or father does not use a parental leave, the leave may be granted to the actual caregiver of the child who lawfully resides in the Republic of Estonia. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Lapsehoolduspuhkust v&otilde;ib kasutada korraga v&otilde;i osade kaupa igal ajal kuni lapse kolmeaastaseks saamiseni. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Parental leave may be used at once or in parts at any time until the child attains three years of age. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Lapsehoolduspuhkust ei anta, kui laps on t&auml;ielikult v&otilde;i osaliselt riiklikul &uuml;lalpidamisel. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) Parental leave is not granted if the child is wholly or partly maintained by the state. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Lapsehoolduspuhkuse ajaks t&ouml;&ouml;leping peatub ja t&ouml;&ouml;tajale makstakse selle aja eest lapsehooldustasuvastavalt riiklike peretoetuste seadusele. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) For the duration of a parental leave, an employment contract is suspended and for this period of time the employee is paid child care allowance pursuant to the State Family Benefits Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(13.10.1999 j&otilde;ust.01.01.2000 - RT I 1999, 82, 749) </eesti>
<inglise>(13.10.1999 entered into force 01.01.2000 - RT I 1999, 82, 749) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 31. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 31. </inglise>
<eesti>T&auml;iendav lapsepuhkus </eesti>
<inglise>Additional child care leave </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Emale v&otilde;i isale antakse tema soovil igal t&ouml;&ouml;aastal t&auml;iendavat lapsepuhkust kolm kalendrip&auml;eva, kui tal on &uuml;ks v&otilde;i kaks alla 14-aastast last, ja kuus kalendrip&auml;eva, kui tal on kolm v&otilde;i enam alla 14-aastast last v&otilde;i v&auml;hemalt &uuml;ks alla kolmeaastane laps. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A mother or father is granted an additional child care leave of three calendar days per working year at his or her request if the mother or father has one or two children under fourteen years of age, and six calendar days if the mother or father has three or more children under fourteen years of age or at least one child under three years of age. </inglise>
<eesti>Sellele puhkusele on &otilde;igus ka lapse eestkostjal, kes kasvatab last ilma vanemateta. </eesti>
<inglise>A guardian raising a child without parents is also entitled to such leave. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Lapse 14-aastaseks saamise aastal antakse t&auml;iendav lapsepuhkus, olenemata sellest, kas lapse s&uuml;nnip&auml;ev on enne v&otilde;i p&auml;rast puhkust. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) An additional child care leave is granted in the year that a child reaches fourteen years of age regardless of whether the child's birthday is before or after the leave. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) T&auml;iendav lapsepuhkus liidetakse p&otilde;hi- ja lisapuhkusele, samuti pikendatud p&otilde;hipuhkusele ja antakse sellega koos v&otilde;i poolte kokkuleppel m&otilde;nel muul ajal. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) An additional child care leave is added to a base holiday, additional holiday and extended base holiday, and is granted together with the same or, by agreement of the parties, at another time. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) T&auml;iendavat lapsepuhkust ei anta, kui laps on t&auml;ielikult v&otilde;i osaliselt riiklikul &uuml;lalpidamisel. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) An additional child care leave is not granted if the child is wholly or partly maintained by the state. </inglise>
<eesti>VI. Palgata ja osaliselt tasustatav puhkus </eesti>
<inglise>VI </inglise>
<eesti>(09.02.93 j&otilde;ust.12.03.93 - RT 1993, 10, 150) </eesti>
<inglise>Holiday without Pay or with Partial Pay </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 32. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 32. </inglise>
<eesti>Palgata puhkus poolte kokkuleppel </eesti>
<inglise>Holiday without pay by agreement of parties </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;tajale v&otilde;ib tema avalduse alusel anda palgata puhkust poolte kokkuleppega m&auml;&auml;ratud ajaks. </eesti>
<inglise>Employees may be granted a holiday without pay at their request for a period of time established by agreement of the parties. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 33. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 33. </inglise>
<eesti>Osaliselt tasustatav puhkus t&ouml;&ouml;andja ettepanekul </eesti>
<inglise>Partially paid holiday on proposal of employer </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;mahu v&otilde;i tellimuste ajutisel v&auml;henemisel v&otilde;ib poolte kokkuleppel ja t&ouml;&ouml;andja asukoha (elukoha) t&ouml;&ouml;inspektori n&otilde;usolekul anda t&ouml;&ouml;tajale osaliselt tasustatavat puhkust kuni kolmeks kuuks, teatades sellest ette v&auml;hemalt kaks n&auml;dalat. </eesti>
<inglise>Upon a temporary decrease in the volume of work or orders, employees may be granted a partially paid holiday for up to three months by agreement of the parties and with the approval of the labour inspector of the employer's location (residence), with at least two weeks' advance notice. </inglise>
<eesti>(09.02.93 j&otilde;ust.12.03.93 - RT 1993, 10, 150) </eesti>
<inglise>(09.02.93 entered into force 12.03.93 - RT 1993, 10, 150) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 34. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 34. </inglise>
<eesti>Palgata puhkuse andmise kohustus </eesti>
<inglise>Duty to grant holiday without pay </inglise>
<eesti>(1) T&ouml;&ouml;andja on kohustatud t&ouml;&ouml;taja soovil andma palgata puhkust: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) At the request of the employee, the employer is required to grant a holiday without pay to: </inglise>
<eesti>1) naisele, kes kasvatab kuni 14-aastast last; </eesti>
<inglise>1) a woman raising a child of up to fourteen years of age; </inglise>
<eesti>2) mehele (eestkostjale), kes kasvatab &uuml;ksinda kuni 14- aastast last; </eesti>
<inglise>2) a man (guardian) raising a child of up to fourteen years of age alone; </inglise>
<eesti>3) &uuml;hele vanematest (eestkostjale, hooldajale), kes kasvatab lapsinvaliidi; </eesti>
<inglise>3) one of the parents (guardian, curator) raising a disabled child; </inglise>
<eesti>4) t&ouml;&ouml;tajale g&uuml;mnaasiumi riigieksamite ning kutse&otilde;ppeasutuse, rakendusliku k&otilde;rgkooli v&otilde;i &uuml;likooli sisseastumiseksamite sooritamiseks; </eesti>
<inglise>4) an employee for taking the state examinations of an upper secondary school or the entrance examinations of a vocational educational institution, institution of applied higher education or a university; </inglise>
<eesti>(03.12.97 j&otilde;ust.03.01.98 - RT I 1997, 93, 1560) </eesti>
<inglise>(03.12.97 entered into force 03.01.98 - RT I 1997, 93, 1560) </inglise>
<eesti>5) muudel seaduse, haldusakti, kollektiiv- v&otilde;i t&ouml;&ouml;lepinguga etten&auml;htud juhtudel. </eesti>
<inglise>5) in other cases prescribed by law, administrative legislation, a collective agreement or employment contract. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi 1. l&otilde;ike punktides 1-3 etten&auml;htud juhtudel antakse palgata puhkust kuni 14 kalendrip&auml;eva t&ouml;&ouml;aasta kestel poolte kokkuleppega m&auml;&auml;ratud ajal. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) In the cases prescribed in clauses (1) 1) -3) of this section, a holiday without pay is granted for up to fourteen calendar days during a working year at a time established by agreement of the parties. </inglise>
<eesti>G&uuml;mnaasiumi riigieksamite ning kutse&otilde;ppeasutuse, rakendusliku k&otilde;rgkooli v&otilde;i &uuml;likooli sisseastumiseksamite sooritamiseks antakse palgata puhkust &otilde;ppeasutuse teatise alusel selles n&auml;idatud ajaks. </eesti>
<inglise>Holidays without pay are granted for taking the state examinations of an upper secondary school or the entrance examinations of a vocational educational institution, institution of applied higher education or a university on the basis of a statement from the educational institution for the time indicated therein. </inglise>
<eesti>Muudel juhtudel antakse palgata puhkust vastavas seaduses, haldusaktis, kollektiiv- v&otilde;i t&ouml;&ouml;lepingus etten&auml;htud ulatuses. </eesti>
<inglise>In other cases, holidays without pay are granted to the extent prescribed in the corresponding Act, administrative legislation, a collective agreement or employment contract. </inglise>
<eesti>(03.12.97 j&otilde;ust.03.01.98 - RT I 1997, 93, 1560) </eesti>
<inglise>(03.12.97 entered into force 03.01.98 - RT I 1997, 93, 1560) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 35. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 35. </inglise>
<eesti>Palgata puhkuse vormistamine </eesti>
<inglise>Formalisation of holiday without pay </inglise>
<eesti>Palgata puhkus vormistatakse t&ouml;&ouml;andja kehtestatud korras. </eesti>
<inglise>Holidays without pay are formalised pursuant to the procedure established by the employer. </inglise>
<eesti>VII. </eesti>
